No Bake Cheesecake
  -Martha Stewart

Crust:
1 1/2 c (8oz) finely ground gingersnap cookies
4 tbsp unsalted butter, melted
3 tbsp sugar

Stir together crumbs, butter, and sugar in a medium bowl. Press firmly onto bottom of 9" springform pan.

Filling:
1 c sugar
2x 8oz cream cheese packages, room temp
3 tbsp fresh lemon juice
1/2 c heavy cream, chilled

Put cream cheese in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with paddle attachment; mix on medium speed until fluffy, ~3 min. With mixer on low speed, add sugar in a slow, steady stream. Add lemon juice; mix until combined. Beat cream in another mixing bowl until stiff peaks form. Gently fold into cream cheese mixture with a rubber spatula. Pour over crust. Freeze 1 hr. Refrigerate until ready to serve, min 30 min.


Notes: can use graham crackers, butter cookies, chocolate wafers, etc.
